00:10:28.040 --> 00:10:30.560
And I think that why this work it, there is a

00:10:30.560 --> 00:10:31.440
lot of things.

00:10:31.560 --> 00:10:33.700
Each of these things will be a talk, but, like

00:10:33.700 --> 00:10:35.400
, I will go very fast through it.

00:10:35.400 --> 00:10:39.160
But there is a coherent consensual product vision, but

00:10:39.160 --> 00:10:42.900
we try to iterate fast knowing that the code is my level

00:10:42.900 --> 00:10:44.560
and we can keep changing it.

00:10:44.580 --> 00:10:47.060
And we use versions so, like, we can iterate in

00:10:47.060 --> 00:10:49.640
main and then, like, when it's ready we release

00:10:49.640 --> 00:10:50.630
it.

00:10:50.650 --> 00:10:53.770
Daniel is extremely good in doing that.

00:10:53.840 --> 00:10:56.540
We lean in conventions, in libraries, like NACs

00:10:56.590 --> 00:10:59.600
, that allow us to go extremely fast and don't discuss

00:10:59.770 --> 00:11:01.560
absolutely every little detail.

00:11:01.580 --> 00:11:05.240
We empower people that care about accessibility, performance, tests.

00:11:05.240 --> 00:11:08.620
If you care about any of these things, come to work

00:11:08.770 --> 00:11:09.480
